# Visualization Research Notes

**Date:** December 10, 2025
**Status:** RESEARCH - Not yet implemented

---

## Goal

Create an immersive "Living Metro System" visualization that:
- Shows Dubai Metro as a living, breathing system
- Makes 12-year planning horizon tangible
- Demonstrates hierarchical planning (strategic → daily)
- Impresses clients visually while proving technical competence

---

## Key Insights from Research

### 1. Hierarchical Planning (Fraunhofer IVI Model)

Source: [Fraunhofer IVI - Decision Support on Three Levels](https://www.ivi.fraunhofer.de/en/research-fields/civil-protection-and-security/infrastructure-management/decision-support-on-the-three-levels-of-maintenance-planning.html)

| Level | Horizon | Focus |
|-------|---------|-------|
| **Strategic** | Years (12 years for Dubai) | Long-term goals, RAMS, LCC, fleet lifecycle |
| **Tactical** | Months to Quarters | Complex maintenance with long lead times, rough schedules |
| **Operational** | Weeks to Days | Dynamic execution, daily adjustments |

**Key Concept:** "Tactical scheduling ensures current resources are allocated efficiently to achieve short-term objectives that support strategic goals."

### 2. Visualization Library Comparison

Source: [D3.js vs Pixi.js Performance](https://blog.octo.com/d3-js-transitions-killed-my-cpu-a-d3-js-pixi-js-comparison)

| Library | Best For | Performance |
|---------|----------|-------------|
| **D3.js** | Data manipulation, SVG charts | Degrades at 1,000+ elements |
| **Pixi.js** | 2D rendering, many elements | 20+ FPS at 10,000+ elements |
| **Three.js** | 3D graphics | WebGL, GPU accelerated |

**Recommendation:** Use D3 for data/layout + Pixi.js for rendering if many elements needed.

### 3. Resource Histogram Pattern

Source: [Resource Histogram in Project Management](https://www.projectmanager.com/blog/what-is-a-resource-histogram)

- Stacked bar chart showing resource usage over time
- Highlights peaks and troughs for leveling decisions
- Used alongside Gantt charts for complete picture

### 4. Gantt Chart for Maintenance

Source: [Gantt Chart for Job Scheduling - Microsoft](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dynamics365/supply-chain/production-control/visual-scheduling-production)

- Empowers planners to control and optimize production
- Makes flow of operations transparent
- Easy to adjust while considering resource constraints

